OL,5,CCumbria
OL,7,FEngland also had endure its second
OL,8,Fdriest spring since Met Office data
OL,9,Fbegan.
OL,11,FIn Cumbria reservoir levels at
OL,12,FHaweswater and Thirlmere were at 44%.
OL,14,FAbout three-quarters of reservoirs or
OL,15,Freservoir groups saw a drop in storage
OL,16,Fof more than 10 percentage points
OL,17,Fduring August, the Environment Agency
OL,18,Fsaid.
